data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both compiled and ran successfully on .NET 11 (preview). The syntax is straightforward:

```csharp
Span<nint>  nints  = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> nuints = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

On this 64-bit system, `nint` is 8 bytes. The only caveat encountered: `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (use `IntPtr.Size` instead in safe code), but the `stackalloc` itself works fine in a safe context when assigned to a `Span<T>`.
